WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Rahul: Good morning everyone. Let’s get started.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Rahul: The goal today is to finalize the mobile app release timeline.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Anjali: Most APIs are done, but we have performance issues under load.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Arun: QA testing showed delays when users exceeded 5,000.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Rahul: How long will it take to fix this?

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Anjali: Around 3 to 4 days for optimization and caching.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Vivek: Frontend is ready, waiting for stable APIs.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Sneha: A short delay is financially acceptable.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Rahul: Should we proceed or delay the release?

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Anjali: I recommend delaying.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Arun: Agree, better to fix now.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Rahul: Decision — delay release by one week.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:05.000
Rahul: Anjali will handle backend optimization.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Anjali: I’ll complete it by April 4.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:15.000
Rahul: Arun will handle QA validation.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Arun: I’ll complete it by April 5.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Rahul: Vivek will prepare the release build.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:30.000
Vivek: I’ll finish by April 6.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:35.000
Rahul: I will notify stakeholders.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Sneha: Include cost estimates in the update.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.000
Rahul: Noted.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:50.000
Rahul: Meeting concluded. Thank you everyone.